               <head>Letters in Persian &amp; English</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary />
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85064914 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85038187 http://lccn.loc.gov/n84029362 http://lccn.loc.gov/n89215273" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3951-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Described on flyleaf at end as: "Copies of Letters from the Navub Mahmood Iridge Khan to Mr. Vansittart, Mr. Hastings and others, Persian ansd English"</p>
                        <p>Collection of original transcripts and English translations of Persian letters from 1) the <term xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">Navvāb</term> [of <name type="place">Murshidābād</name>] to <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7746" role="rcp">Vansittart</persName> (ff. 1r, 5r,7r, 14v, 20v), <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_29571391" role="rcp">Hastings</persName> (ff. 37r, 67r), <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7690" role="aut">Lieutenant Ironside</persName> (f. 24v), also a <term xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc">naql-i dastak</term> of Navvāb <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7729" role="rcp">Qāsim Khān Bahādur</persName>, dated <date calendar="Hijri qamari">23 Z̲ī al-ḥijjah year 3</date> (f. 24v); 2) addressed to <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7684" role="rcp">Ironside</persName> from "<persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7681" role="aut">Goorgeen Chan</persName>" (f. 26v), <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7670" role="aut">ʿAlī Mīrzā Khān</persName>(f. 69r), "<persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7695" role="aut">Mahmud [sic, read Muḥammad] Iridge Cawn</persName>, Naib of <name type="place">Murshudabad</name>" (ff. 77r, 80v, 84), <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7680" role="aut">Ghulām Ḥusayn Khān</persName> (f. 78v, 81r), "<persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7694" role="aut">Mahmud [sic, read Muḥammad] Ali</persName>, <term xml:lang="en">Foujdar</term> of <name type="place">Dacca</name>" (f. 30v)
                        </p>
                        <p>Most letters undated, except for 2: 1) f. 66v is dated <date calendar="Hijri qamari">8 Z̲ī al-qaʿdah 1176</date> / <date calendar="Gregorian">1763</date>; 2) f. 20v mentions the month of <date calendar="Gregorian">Kārtik Bikram samvat 1167</date> as being 16 months before the month of <date calendar="Gregorian">Māgh</date> to the year of writing
                        </p>
                        <p>Undated</p>
                     </note>
